data.event: The Erie Canal opened in 1825, making a ready market for wheat and lumber.

event.title: was begun at the Kendall Settlement in 1825

data.event: The first Norwegian immigrant community in the United States was begun at the Kendall Settlement in 1825.

event.title: founded a settlement in the Fox River Valley of Illinois during 1834

data.event: Norwegian-American pioneer leader Cleng Peerson subsequently founded a settlement in the Fox River Valley of Illinois during 1834, near the community of Norway, Illinois.

event.title: April 7, 1837, about half of the Town of Murray became

data.event: On April 7, 1837, about half of the Town of Murray became the new Town of Kendall.
